Part 1 - Creating tidy data using tidyr

Tuition <- tuition_cost %>%
  pivot_longer(cols = starts_with("20"),
               names_to = "Year",
               values_to = "tuition") %>%
  separate(tuition, into = c("InState", "OutState"), sep = "/", convert = TRUE)
head(Tuition)
## # A tibble: 6  8
##   name               state state_code type  degree_length Year  InState OutState

Part 2 - North Carolina Schools

Public <- Tuition %>%
  filter(type == "Public" & state == "North Carolina" & degree_length == "4 Year")
head(Public)
## # A tibble: 6  8
##   name               state state_code type  degree_length Year  InState OutState
##   <chr>              <chr> <chr>      <chr> <chr>         <chr>   <dbl>    <dbl>
## 1 Appalachian State Nort NC         Publ 4 Year        2017    7214    22021 
## 2 Appalachian State Nort NC         Publ 4 Year        2018    8657.   27526.
## 3 Appalachian State Nort NC         Publ 4 Year        2019    9522.   30279.
## 4 Appalachian State Nort NC         Publ 4 Year        2020   11903.   31793.
## 5 East Carolina Uni Nort NC         Publ 4 Year        2017    7188    23465 
## 6 East Carolina Uni Nort NC         Publ 4 Year        2018    8626.   29331.
ggplot(Public, aes(x = Year, y = InState, color = name)) +
  geom_point() +
  labs(
    title = "In-State Tuition for North Carolina Schools",
    x= "Year",
    y = "Cost in $"
  ) +
  theme(legend.title = element_blank())

UNC <- filter(Public,grepl("University of North Carolina",name))
ggplot(UNC, aes(x = Year, y = InState, color = name)) +
  geom_point() +
  labs(
    title = "In-State Tuition for UNC Schools",
    x = "Year",
    y = "Cost in $"
  ) +
  theme(legend.title = element_blank(),
        legend.position = "bottom"
        ) +
        guides(colour = guide_legend(nrow = 4))
